<L>__{interior bathhouse furnace day}
<A>__{this is another, bigger fire. in fact we might be in hell. a crude furnace blazes. filthy, sweat covered men feed it with wood and charcoal, an endless task given the ferocity of the fire. to one side of the oppressive, low ceilinged furnace room, some small boys endlessly toil at two large bellows, feeding the flames with jets of air. over the noise of the furnace someone is whistling, an odd human sound in an inhuman setting. shadowy figures come and go with barrow loads of wood. we tilt up to the space above the furnace to see a mass of dangerously crude clay pipes, oozing water and steam at every jointerior}
